label.value: abnormal 5' deoxyribonuclease (pyrimidine dimer) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 5' deoxyribonuclease (pyrimidine dimer) activity is abnormal.

label.value: abolished 5' deoxyribonuclease (pyrimidine dimer) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which 5' deoxyribonuclease (pyrimidine dimer) activity is absent.

label.value: decreased 5' deoxyribonuclease (pyrimidine dimer) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 5' deoxyribonuclease (pyrimidine dimer) activity is decreased.

label.value: decreased UV-damage excision repair

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which UV-damage excision repair occurs to a lower extent than normal. UV-damage excision repair is a DNA repair process that is initiated by an endonuclease that introduces a single-strand incision immediately 5' of a UV-induced damage site, and that acts on both cyclobutane pyrimidine dimers (CPDs) and pyrimidine-pyrimidone 6-4 photoproducts (6-4PPs).

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at rDNA

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at ribosomal DNA repeat regions is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at tRNA genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at tRNA genes is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased glutathione transferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione transferase activity is decreased.

label.value: abnormal thioredoxin-disulfide reductase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of thioredoxin-disulfide reductase activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased thioredoxin-disulfide reductase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of thioredoxin-disulfide reductase activity is increased.

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to mercury ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to mercury ions is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of increase in RNA level during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cell phenotype in which an increase in RNA level that occurs as part of a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide begins later than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

label.value: abolished primary amine oxidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which primary amine oxidase activity is absent.

label.value: mitotic cell cycle arrest phenotype

value.value: A cell cycle phenotype that affects or involves the normal or abnormal occurrence of mitotic cell cycle arrest. In mitotic cell cycle arrest, progression through the mitotic cell cycle is halted during one of the normal phases (G1, S, G2, or M).

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype.

label.value: normal primary amine oxidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a primary amine oxidase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: fragmented septum

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell forms pieces of a septum rather than a septum that completely bisects the cell.

label.value: tetranucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains four nuclei.

label.value: elongated tetranucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains four nuclei and is elongated.

label.value: elongated tetranucleate vegetative cell with fragmented septum

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which vegetative a cell is elongated, and contains four nuclei and pieces of a septum that does not completely bisect the cell.

label.value: tetranucleate vegetative cell with fragmented septum

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains four nuclei and pieces of a septum that does not completely bisect the cell.

label.value: binucleate vegetative cell with fragmented septum

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains two nuclei and pieces of a septum that does not completely bisect the cell.

label.value: abnormal glutathione peroxidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione peroxidase activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased glutathione peroxidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione peroxidase activity is increased.

label.value: decreased glutathione transferase activity during stationary phase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione transferase activity is decreased in a cell culture in stationary phase.

label.value: increased glutathione transferase activity during stationary phase

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glutathione transferase activity is increased in a cell culture in stationary phase.

label.value: RNA absent from cell during cellular response to hydrogen peroxide

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is too low to detect during a cellular response to hydrogen peroxide. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abolished during a cellular response to salt stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during a cellular response to salt stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased intragenic meiotic recombination

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of intragenic meiotic recombination is increased. Intragenic meiotic recombination can result in gene conversion events.

label.value: decreased meiotic recombination at CRE promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of reciprocal meiotic recombination at a CRE promoter in a chromosome is decreased.

label.value: normal meiotic recombination at CRE promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which reciprocal meiotic recombination is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) at an CRE promoter in a chromosome.

label.value: abolished endocytosis during meiotic interphase II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which endocytosis does not occur during meiotic interphase II, i.e. the phase between the end of meiosis I cytokinesis the beginning of meiosis II prophase. A phenotype may affect endocytosis of all cargoes, or of specific cargo such as a particular protein.

label.value: decreased UV-damage excision repair during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which UV-damage excision repair occurs to a lower extent than normal during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle. UV-damage excision repair is a DNA repair process that is initiated by an endonuclease that introduces a single-strand incision immediately 5' of a UV-induced damage site, and that acts on both cyclobutane pyrimidine dimers (CPDs) and pyrimidine-pyrimidone 6-4 photoproducts (6-4PPs).

label.value: increased duration of protein phosphorylation during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of protein phosphorylation is longer than normal during a cellular response to salt stress. All phosphorylation may be affected, or only phosphorylation of specific proteins, or even specific sites within specific proteins.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to cytoplasm during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to all or part of the cytoplasm is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to salt stress.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal transcription during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription of RNA from one or more DNA templates is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal transcription elongation from RNA polymerase II promoter

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the elongation of a transcript initiated from an RNA polymerase II promoter is abnormal.

label.value: increased protein localization to chromatin at protein coding gene

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at one or more protein-coding genes is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 2 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: decreased phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 5 residues during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 5 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abolished phosphorylation of RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain serine 2 residues

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of the serine residue at position 2 within one or more copies of the heptapeptide repeat (YSPTSPS) of the C-terminal domain of RNA polymerase II does not occur.

label.value: RNA absent from cell during cellular response to copper ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is too low to detect during a cellular response to copper ion starvation. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to copper ion during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to copper ions is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: RNA absent from cell during cellular response to pheromone

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell is too low to detect during a cellular response to a pheromone. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: two cell divisions prior to cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase in response to pheromone

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of cell cycle arrest in response to a pheromone occurs in G1 phase, but begins only after the cells have undergone two rounds of cell division in the presence of the pheromone.

label.value: delayed onset of cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase in response to pheromone

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of cell cycle arrest in response to a pheromone occurs in G1 phase, but begins later than normal.

definition.value: This term can be used for any circumstances in which cells are starved for nitrogen. Note that cells may enter G0 (quiescence) when subjected to prolonged nitrogen starvation; this term is not restricted to G0.

label.value: decreased cell growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cell growth is decreased. Cell growth is the irreversible increase in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter similar to that already present.

definition.value: Note that this term refers to growth, i.e. increase in size, of an individual cell. If you have measured the rate or extent of growth of a culture in liquid medium or on plates, use one of the 'cell population growth' terms.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, elongated multiseptate cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is elongated, has more than one septum, and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division.

label.value: abnormal sporulation resulting in formation of ascus with single large spore

value.value: A sporulation phenotype that results in the formation of an ascus that contains a single spore that is larger than normal.

label.value: normal growth on cyclosporin A

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing cyclosporin A.
